 let’s lay out a step‑by‑step development plan for your Neighborhood Tycoon game,
using the stack we discussed (Unity + Firebase + AdMob + PlayFab). This roadmap will take you from concept to Play Store launch:

🗓️ Development Roadmap
Week 1–2: Foundation
Set up Unity project (2D or light 3D simulation style).

Design core UI wireframes (Home, Build Shop, Upgrade, Leaderboard).

Implement basic shop building:

Place a kiosk or suya stand.

Generate coins over time.

Local data storage: Use SQLite or Unity PlayerPrefs for offline progress.

Week 3–4: Core Gameplay
Upgrade system: Shops can be leveled up to increase coin output.

Economy balancing: Adjust coin generation rates so gameplay feels rewarding but not too easy.

Basic leaderboard (local): Show rankings within the device.

First-time user journey: Tutorial + onboarding rewards.

Week 5–6: Monetization
Integrate Google AdMob:

Rewarded ads (double coins).

Interstitial ads (between upgrades).

Google Play Billing:

Premium shops (Mega Mall, National Museum).

Skins/decorations.

Test purchases in sandbox mode.

Week 7–8: Social & Viral Features
Firebase Authentication: Player accounts via email/Google login.

Firebase Dynamic Links: Invite friends → both get rewards.

Screenshot sharing plugin: Share estate images to WhatsApp/Instagram.

PlayFab Leaderboards: Global rankings across all players.

Week 9–10: Events & Seasonal Content
Event system: Independence Day pack (flags, fireworks, parade).

Daily challenges: “Decorate 3 shops today.”

Season pass: Exclusive rewards for subscribers.

Push notifications: “Your Suya Stand is ready to serve customers!”

Week 11–12: Testing & Launch
Beta testing: Small group of friends/students.

Bug fixes & polish: Smooth animations, balanced economy.

Analytics setup: Track retention, ad engagement, purchases.

Play Store submission: Prepare screenshots, description, and marketing assets.

🚀 Post-Launch Growth
Weekly events (Christmas, New Year, Easter).

Partnerships with local brands (MTN shop, Coca-Cola kiosk).

Community feedback loop: Add features players request (co-op estates, pranks).
